<HL>
   Business Brief -- Ford Motor Co.:
   ABB Flakt Unit Receives
   Contract for Firm's Facility
</HL>
<DATE>
09/18/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   S.FLK F FLR S.ABB
</CO>
<IN>
AUTO PARTS AND EQUIPMENT INCLUDING TIRES (AUP)
</IN>
<LP>
   A division of ABB Flakt Inc. said Ford Motor Co. awarded
it a $200 million contract to complete a paint finishing
facility at Ford's Oakville, Ontario, assembly plant.
   The 641,000-square-foot facility will be located near the
assembly plant that builds the Ford Tempo and Mercury Topaz
models, said ABB Flakt Alpha, a division of ABB Flakt. The
building is expected to be completed by January 1992.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   ABB Flakt, an Atlanta provider of paint finishing systems
for the automotive industry, said it will administer the
contract, in part, through a joint venture with Fluor Daniel
Inc., a Greenville, S.C., engineering, construction and
technical services subsidiary of Fluor Corp.
</TEXT>
